content.description: Start on the same boulder as Jug-Yur-Not, but climb the face to the left.
content.protection: No gear, standard gear to set up an anchor.
content.location: Start on the same boulder as Jug-Yur-Not.

content.description: This is the obvious chimney to the right of "Jug-Yur-Not". A fun chimney for beginners. Down climb to the right, then down the backside to descend.
content.protection:
3" to 5" cams. There are bolted anchors on top both to the left and to the right.

Getting to the anchor is probably the crux. Easiest to solo.

content.description: A mystery route.  Used to have 1/4" buttonhead bolts with wire rivet hangers.  Now there are three bolts to a bolted anchor.  Boulder up the crack/chimney to the right....clip the bolt and pop over onto the face.  Climb up past two more bolts to the anchor.
content.protection: Three bolts. Quickdraws. Two-bolt anchor. Walk-off decent.

climbs.name: Stud Muffin
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon and Cyndie Bransford, October 1990

content.description: Start off a boulder between "Jaime Crack" and "Jaime's Big Show". Climb face past two bolts.

climbs.name: Square Headache
climbs.fa: Todd Swain, Randy Ziedberg, Andy Schenkel 03-28-1991

content.description: Start about 20 feet left of Wine in a Box. Climb an overhang (crux), then hand traverse left (8) to gain an easy, right leaning crack.
content.location: Start about 20 feet left of Wine in a Box (the same spot as Jug-Yur-Not, atop a boulder).

content.description: Climb the plated face to the right of Knappa Valley, the easy crack.
content.location: Start to the right of Knappa Valley.

content.description: This is the wide Chimney/Offwidth crack in the box canyon North wall.
content.protection: some small cams can be arranged deep within the crack.
content.location: In the box canyon South of Jame's rock there is a short wide chimney/offwidth located on the N. wall.

climbs.name: Monkey Toes  (aka Wet Your Whistle)
climbs.fa: FA: Todd Swain, Randy Ziedberg, Andy Schenkel Mar 28, 1991   FA (bolts)  Charlie Richardson , et al

content.description:
Located just right of

Unnamed Chimney

and left of

Knappa Valley

and

Sip, Don't Guzzle
content.protection: three bolts to a bolted anchor.
content.location: Across from north face of Picnic Rock and far right of Circle Rock.

content.description: Boulder up past bulge to get on the face and past a bolt to the top.
content.protection: Bring small gear and you can protect the crux at the bottom. Gear to 2 inches for the top.
content.location: Located just to the right of the alcove containing Box Canyon Crack and 20' left on the same wall as Jug-Yur-Not. Walk off climbers left.

content.description: This route is a cool little out of the way INTRO to climbing spot. Great for a confidence booster for the kiddies. Easy to TR and easy to climb.
content.protection: Gear from 1/2" up to 3", bolts on top for anchor.
content.location: From group camp one walk around to the left and around the formation this climb faces south. It lies 25' right of Jug-Yur-Not and a big chimney. From Pixie head northwest you will see it.

content.description: This is on a small formation about 50 yards to the right of JaimeÂ’s Rock. From the top of a boulder, step across into a flared crack, and then follow thin cracks to the top. There is a bolted anchor on top.
content.protection: Light rack to 2". There's a 2-bolt anchor at the top.

content.description: Face climb, crux is the slab between the first and second bolts. Shares an anchor with Easter Overflow. Anchor has no rings. Traverse a few feet left and lower off the top of Easter Egg Hunt (Jamie Manuever).
content.location: Bolted route to the right of Easter Overflow, left of Jamie's Crack.

content.description:
This is the first crack to the right of "Easter Overflow".

A scary lead for beginners.

climbs.name: Jaime's Big Show
climbs.fa: Jaime Lara, Warren Mellinger & Ben Chapman, April 1986

content.description: This climbs the crack on the right side of the face, passing a bulge near the bottom.

climbs.name: Easter Overflow
climbs.fa: Louie Anderson, David Larson & Diana Larson, April 1990

content.description:
This is the first route encountered when approaching from GC Site #1.

Face climb past 4 bolts. The 5.9 start moves can be avoided by traversing in from the right, to the second bolt.

climbs.name: Easter Egg Hunt (aka Jaime Maneuver)
climbs.fa: (TR) Todd Swain, Randy Ziedberg, Andy Schenkel, 03-28-1991, FL: Todd Gordon, Karen Miller & Maggie Ross, October 1999

content.description: The line follows the left portion of Easter Overflow.  There is some traversing involved between the 2nd and 3rd bolt.  The start is much easier than EO.  Not 100% sure but I believe first ascent was Todd Gordon.  Such a fun route didn't want it to be missed here.
content.location: Located on Jaime's rock behind group camp site #1 in Indian Cove It is the route to the left of Easter Overflow.

content.description: Start about 10 feet right of Sip, Don't Guzzle at a nose. Climb the nose.
content.location: Start about 10 feet right of Sip, Don't Guzzle at a nose.

climbs.name: Box Canyon Crack
climbs.fa: Ben Chapman, Jaime Lara, Sue Ann Murray and Dick Seward, April 1986

content.description:
This crack is in the small box canyon to the right of Jaime's Rock.

Climb the obvious, south facing crack with a small bush.

Crux is after a fairly high first bolt.  Small crimpers make for a fairly difficult move on an almost vertical face.

Make sure to rap down.  Rope drag just below the anchors would be appalling, as a sharp ledge of petina lies directly below the anchors.
